                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115/12–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-19T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 19, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2581. Senator Green of Rhode Island has expressed strong interest in case of Jan
                    Czechel. Please renew representations with Soviet authorities with view to
                    obtaining exist visa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
